Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm chunks.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve any thick @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%grams} stems lengthways and pop onto a large #baking tray{} with the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%grams}. Sprinkle over half the garlic. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Set aside.

Drain the @Fish Pie Mix{1%pack}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

> If you'd prefer to boil your broccoli, boil it in step 5 while the pie is in the oven for 3-5 mins, until tender.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @Korma Curry Paste{50%grams}, @Curry Powder Mix{1%sachet} and remaining garlic. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%grams}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{15%grams} and @Water for the Sauce{100%milliliter(s)}. Bring to the boil and simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the fish pie mix, @Peas{120%grams} and @Mango Chutney{40%grams}. Remove from the heat. Transfer to an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{}.

Carefully wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to medium heat.

Melt the @Butter{30%grams}, then add the @Mustard Seeds{1%sachet} and cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Pour in the mustard seed butter and add a splash of @?milk{}. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

Top the fish mixture with an even layer of mash, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until piping hot and cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

At the same time, roast the broccoli and tomatoes on the middle shelf until tender and softened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once the pie is out of the oven, allow it to stand for ~{2%minutes}.

Share the Indian inspired fish pie between your plates.

Serve the roasted broccoli and tomatoes alongside.

Enjoy!